{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Set a small bowl on mixing bowl lid, weigh in 100 g water and set aside.","Place garlic cloves, cayenne pepper and coriander in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Remove 2 heaped tsp, add to small bowl with water and set aside to soak.","Add spinach, olive oil and ½ tsp salt to mixing bowl and mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl using spatula and mix again <nobr>10 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr> to obtain a coarse spinach paste.","Pour reserved soaking mixture through simmering basket into another small bowl and set the spicy liquid aside. Return contents of simmering basket to mixing bowl. Spread half the spinach paste onto the middle of a large piece of baking paper (30 cm x 45 cm), place fish on top and cover with remaining spinach paste. Fold up paper and twist ends to make a closed parcel. Place butterfly whisk flat in Varoma dish and add fish parcel on top of whisk, to ensure some holes remain unobstructed.","Place 500 g water in mixing bowl, insert simmering basket and add potatoes to it. Set Varoma in position and steam <nobr>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Meanwhile, add turmeric, chickpea flour, sugar, remaining ½ tsp salt, pepper and lemon juice to reserved spicy liquid in small bowl, and arrange carrots and broccoli on Varoma tray.","Carefully remove Varoma lid and insert Varoma tray. Close Varoma and steam <nobr>8 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Carefully remove Varoma lid and tray and set aside to check that fish and vegetables are cooked - fish should flake easily. If needed, steam again <nobr>2-5 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Transfer potatoes, vegetables and fish parcel to a warm serving dish and keep warm while making the sauce. Discard steaming water.","Place Greek yoghurt and reserved spicy liquid in mixing bowl and cook <nobr>8 min\/90°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Adjust seasoning as desired and serve fish, potatoes and vegetables with sauce, garnishing with a few fresh coriander leaves."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["600 g water","2 garlic cloves (approx. 5 g total)","¼ - ½ tsp ground cayenne pepper","50 g fresh coriander, plus extra to garnish","100 g fresh baby spinach","40 g olive oil","1 tsp salt","600 g white fish fillets (e.g. halibut, haddock, cod, 1 cm thick), skinless, boneless","400 g potatoes, new or waxy, cut in small pieces (1 cm)","¼ tsp ground turmeric","4 tsp chickpea flour (approx. 15 g, see tip)","1 tsp sugar","½ tsp freshly ground pepper, plus extra to taste","2 tsp lemon juice","200 g carrots, cut in slices (1 cm thick)","200 g broccoli florets, cut in pieces (3 cm)","250 g Greek yoghurt"]}],"id":"r90170","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/--xCZ7SsJlcE\/XZVPpCNVRvI\/AAAAAAAAc7E\/HuyqVPOUwAsoekd6KJDBSYFieOSYdEviQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_BKcW_fRUj7DhkqXP.png","title":"Indian-style fish with yoghurt sauce, potatoes and vegetables","publishedAt":"2017-07-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"36 g","fat":"18 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"28 g","calories":"1830 kJ \/ 437 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking paper","hintsAndTricks":["Here we use the butterfly whisk lying flat in the Varoma dish to ensure good steam circulation around a baking paper parcel - a good trick to remember for your own recipes. Serve this easy meal with naans or soft bread to soak up the tasty green paste and sauce, and feel free to use our tip to make a spicy dinner for two if you prefer.","To make chickpea flour, grind <nobr>100 g dried<\/nobr> chickpeas <nobr><strong>3 min\/speed 10<\/strong><\/nobr> and store extra in a glass jar for another use.","To <nobr>serve 2,<\/nobr> halve all ingredients except steaming water. In <nobr>step 7,<\/nobr> cook for <nobr>6 minutes.<\/nobr>","If fresh fish is not available, use frozen fish which has been defrosted.","Replace carrots and broccoli with vegetables of your choice with similar steaming time.","Omit coriander and replace with extra spinach."],"basicInfo":["medium",